   "source": [
    "# 🤖 Semantic FAQ Bot\n",
    "\n",
    "A lightweight FAQ-matching chatbot built with **Sentence Transformers** and **cosine similarity**.\n",
    "Instead of relying on exact keyword matches, the bot converts every question into a dense vector\n",
    "embedding and retrieves the FAQ entry that is semantically closest to the user's query — so it can\n",
    "understand paraphrases, abbreviations, and loosely-worded questions.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Example:**\n",
    "\n",
    "| User asks | Bot matches | \n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| `\"ML\"` | *What is Machine Learning?* |\n",
    "| `\"NLP Stands for?\"` | *What is NLP?* |\n",
    "| `\"What is RAG in Computer Science?\"` | *What is RAG?* |\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## How it works\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Embed** every FAQ question in the knowledge base into a 384-dimensional vector using the\n",
    "   pre-trained `all-MiniLM-L6-v2` Sentence Transformer model.\n",
    "2. **Embed** the user's query the same way.\n",
    "3. **Compare** the query vector against all FAQ vectors using cosine similarity.\n",
    "4. **Return** the answer linked to the most similar FAQ question, along with a confidence score.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Tech stack\n",
    "- [`sentence-transformers`](https://www.sbert.net/) — pre-trained embedding model (`all-MiniLM-L6-v2`)\n",
    "- `scikit-learn` — cosine similarity\n",
    "- `numpy` — vector operations\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "581e942c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Imports"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "60edeee1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity\n",
    "import numpy as np\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1e8bb0bd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Load the embedding model\n",
    "\n",
    "`all-MiniLM-L6-v2` is a small, fast Sentence Transformer that maps sentences to a\n",
    "384-dimensional dense vector space. It offers a strong accuracy/speed trade-off, which makes\n",
    "it ideal for lightweight semantic search applications like this one."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "fcc4248c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model = SentenceTransformer(\"all-MiniLM-L6-v2\")\n",
    "print(\"Model loaded successfully.\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e6814542",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
