   "source": [
    "## 4. Encode the FAQ questions\n",
    "\n",
    "All FAQ questions are embedded **once** and cached in memory. This is important for performance:\n",
    "re-encoding the entire knowledge base on every user query (as a naive implementation might) would\n",
    "be wasteful — here it's done a single time and reused for every lookup."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "ceb7d8d7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "question_embeddings = model.encode(questions)\n",
    "print(\"Shape of FAQ question embeddings:\", question_embeddings.shape)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c66e77e3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. The `ask_question()` function\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the core matching function. Given a user query, it:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Encodes the query into a vector.\n",
    "2. Compares it against the **already-computed** `question_embeddings` (no re-encoding of the\n",
    "   whole FAQ list on every call — a performance fix over a naive first draft).\n",
    "3. Finds the best-matching FAQ question and its similarity score.\n",
    "4. Prints the **Question**, **Matched Question**, **Match Score**, and **Answer**.\n",
    "5. If the match score falls below `MIN_CONFIDENCE`, it prints a polite \"sorry, I don't know\n",
    "   that one\" message instead of guessing."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "a59293f7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "MIN_CONFIDENCE = 0.35  # similarity scores below this are treated as \"no confident match\"\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def ask_question(query: str) -> None:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Find and print the best-matching FAQ answer for a user's query.\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    query_embedding = model.encode([query])\n",
    "    similarity = cosine_similarity(query_embedding, question_embeddings)\n",
    "\n",
    "    best_match_index = np.argmax(similarity)\n",
    "    best_score = round(float(similarity[0][best_match_index]), 3)\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(\"Question       :\", query)\n",
    "\n",
    "    if best_score < MIN_CONFIDENCE:\n",
    "        print(\"Matched Question:\", \"-\")\n",
    "        print(\"Match Score     :\", best_score)\n",
    "        print(\"Answer          :\", \"Sorry, I don't have an answer for that. Could you rephrase your question?\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print(\"Matched Question:\", questions[best_match_index])\n",
    "        print(\"Match Score     :\", best_score)\n",
    "        print(\"Answer          :\", answers[best_match_index])\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(\"-\" * 80)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "704c8092",
